Special Assistant to the President and Coordinator for the Southwest Border, Ambassador Roberta Jacobson, along with Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for the Western Hemisphere Juan Gonzalez and Department of State Northern Triangle Special Envoy Ricardo Zuniga, traveled to Mexico on March 22. Their purpose was to engage with Mexican government officials and develop a plan to effectively and humanely manage migration. During their visit, they met with officials from the Foreign Ministry, the National Institute of Migration, and Mexico's development agency, AMEXCID, to discuss the challenges and address the root causes of irregular migration.